Container Orchestration-->
A container  orchestration technology that manages  and deploys  thousands of  container in cluster.




Node -  A node is a machine , physical or virtual  on which kubernetes is installed . A node is a worker machine  and that is  where  containers will be launched by kubernetes.
It was also known as minions in the past. 

Cluster -  A cluster is  a set of nodes  grouped together . This way , even if one node fails , you have your application still accesible from the other nodes.  Moreover , having multiple nodes helps in sharing loads as well .

Master -  The Master  is another node with kubernetes installed in it and is configured as a master. the master watches over the nodes in the cluster and is responsible for the actual orchastration of containers on the worker nodes. When you install  kubernetes  on a system you are actually installing the following components , an API server and etcd  service , a kubelet service ,  a container runtime , controllers and scedulers. 
The API  server acts  as the front end for kubernetes.



Components -->

Api Server -> The API server acts as a frontend for kubernetes. The user management devices , command line interfaces , all talk to the API server to interact with kubernetes cluster .

etcd -> etcd is a distributed reliable key-value store used by kubernetes to store all data used to manage the cluster. When you have multple node and multiple masters in your cluster , etcd stores all that information on all the nodes in the cluster in a distributed manner .  etcd is responsible for implementing locks within the cluster to ensure that there are no conflicts between the masters.

Scheduler ->  The Scheculer is responsible for distributing work or containers across multiple nodes. It looks for newly created containers and assigns them to nodes. 

Controller -> The controller are the brain orchestration. They are responsible for noticing and responding when  nodes , containers or endpoints go down. The  controller make decisions to bring up new containers in such cases . 

Container Runtime -> The container runtime is the underlying software that is used to run containers.

kubelet -> kubelet is the agent that runs  on each node in the cluster. The agent is responsible for making sure that the  containers are running on the nodes as expected  




