ūüß† 1. Control Plane (Master Node)
This is the brain of Kubernetes.
It takes decisions like:
	‚ÄĘ Where to run Pods
	‚ÄĘ Restart failed Pods
	‚ÄĘ Maintain desired replicas
	‚ÄĘ Handle cluster state
Control Plane has 5 main components:

1ÔłŹ‚É£ API Server
ūüďĆ ‚ÄúFront door of Kubernetes‚ÄĚ
	‚ÄĘ All kubectl commands go to the API server
	‚ÄĘ Other components talk to API Server
	‚ÄĘ Validates & saves cluster objects (pods, deployments, etc.)

2ÔłŹ‚É£ ETCD
ūüďĆ ‚ÄúDatabase of the cluster‚ÄĚ
	‚ÄĘ A distributed key-value store
	‚ÄĘ Stores entire cluster state
(pods, nodes, configs, secrets, deployments)
If ETCD is lost ‚Üí cluster information is lost.

3ÔłŹ‚É£ Scheduler
ūüďĆ ‚ÄúDecides where to run Pods‚ÄĚ
	‚ÄĘ Looks at all available nodes
	‚ÄĘ Chooses the best worker node
Based on:
	‚ÄĘ CPU / RAM availability
	‚ÄĘ Node taints/tolerations
	‚ÄĘ Pod resource requests & limits

4ÔłŹ‚É£ Controller Manager
ūüďĆ ‚ÄúEnsures desired state‚ÄĚ
Example:
If you want 3 pods and 1 pod crashes ‚Üí
Controller Manager will recreate it.
Contains many controllers:
	‚ÄĘ Node Controller
	‚ÄĘ Deployment Controller
	‚ÄĘ ReplicaSet Controller
	‚ÄĘ Job Controller

5ÔłŹ‚É£ Cloud Controller Manager
ūüďĆ Connects Kubernetes with cloud providers (AWS, GCP, Azure)
Used for:
	‚ÄĘ Load balancers
	‚ÄĘ Volumes (EBS, etc.)
	‚ÄĘ Cloud networking

ūüĖ•ÔłŹ 2. Worker Nodes
Worker nodes actually run your applications.
Each worker node has 3 components:

1ÔłŹ‚É£ Kubelet
ūüďĆ ‚ÄúKubernetes agent running on each worker node‚ÄĚ
Responsibilities:
	‚ÄĘ Watches for new tasks from Control Plane
	‚ÄĘ Starts containers using container runtime
	‚ÄĘ Reports node and pod health

2ÔłŹ‚É£ Container Runtime
ūüďĆ The software that actually runs containers.
Examples:
	‚ÄĘ containerd (default)
	‚ÄĘ Docker
	‚ÄĘ CRI-O
Kubernetes does not run containers, runtime does.

3ÔłŹ‚É£ Kube-Proxy
ūüďĆ ‚ÄúNetwork traffic router‚ÄĚ
	‚ÄĘ Handles networking rules
	‚ÄĘ Enables service discovery
	‚ÄĘ Load balances traffic between Pods

ūüßĪ How Kubernetes Works (Step-by-step)
1ÔłŹ‚É£ You run:

