ūüź≥ Docker vs containerd (Easy Explanation)
‚≠ź First, understand the relationship:
ūüĎČ Docker uses containerd internally.
containerd is a core container runtime, while Docker is a complete container platform.

ūüßĪ 1. What is Docker?
Docker is a full container platform that includes:
	‚ÄĘ Docker CLI (docker)
	‚ÄĘ Docker daemon (dockerd)
	‚ÄĘ containerd (as runtime)
	‚ÄĘ Build system
	‚ÄĘ Networking
	‚ÄĘ Volumes
	‚ÄĘ Registry integration
‚≠ź Docker = Full toolset to build, run & manage containers.

ūüßĪ 2. What is containerd?
containerd is a lightweight container runtime.
It is responsible only for:
	‚ÄĘ Running containers
	‚ÄĘ Pulling images
	‚ÄĘ Managing container lifecycle
It does not include:
	‚ÄĘ CLI
	‚ÄĘ Build system
	‚ÄĘ Swarm
	‚ÄĘ Networking configuration (only basic)
‚≠ź containerd = The engine that actually runs containers.

ūüß© 3. Why Kubernetes prefers containerd?
	‚ÄĘ Lighter
	‚ÄĘ Faster
	‚ÄĘ No Docker daemon needed
	‚ÄĘ Kubernetes directly talks to containerd
	‚ÄĘ Less overhead
	‚ÄĘ Follows CRI (Container Runtime Interface) standard
Since 2022, Kubernetes removed Docker support‚ÄĒbut it still supports containerd (Docker‚Äôs runtime).

