ūüĒ• 1. CRI (Container Runtime Interface)
What is CRI?
CRI = Container Runtime Interface
A standard API that Kubelet uses to talk to container runtimes.
Why CRI exists?
Earlier Kubernetes supported only Docker.
But every cluster shouldn't depend on Docker, so CRI was introduced.
Kubelet talks to:
Kubelet ‚Üí	Talks to
Docker	Using dockershim (deprecated)
Containerd	Using CRI plugin
CRI-O	Using CRI plugin

ūüĒ• 2. DockerShim (DEPRECATED)
Before Kubernetes v1.24
Kubelet used Docker indirectly using a component called dockershim.
But now:
‚úĒ dockershim removed
‚úĒ Docker directly NOT supported
‚úĒ containerd/CRI-O is the default runtime

