A Replication Controller (RC) is an old Kubernetes object used to make sure that a specified number of Pod replicas are always running.
ūüĎČ If 3 pods must run ‚Üí RC ensures 3 pods are running always.


ūüü• Replication Controller is OLD (Deprecated)
ūüöę RC is outdated.
‚úĒ Today we use ReplicaSet (RS) and Deployment.



ReplicationController	ReplicaSet
Old	New
Less features	Supports selectors, rolling updates
Not used in modern Kubernetes	Used under Deployment



Replication means running multiple identical copies of a Pod to ensure:
	1. High availability (if one pod dies, others keep running)
	2. Load distribution (traffic gets shared across replicas)
	3. Auto-healing (Kubernetes replaces failed pods automatically)



